	        <table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Contributing Writer, Business 2.0</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Mr. Keighley, recently named one of the "Top 30 Journalists Under 30" by TJFR Group, covers the convergence between entertainment and technology with a specific focus on the videogame industry.  He currently serves as a contributing writer to Business 2.0 and Entertainment Weekly, and is the monthly back-page columnist for the Official Xbox Magazine. On television he is the host of Game Head (SpikeTV), a correspondent on The Electric Playground (G4) and an expert on the entertainment newsmagazine Extra (NBC).  Keighley, who has covered videogames for more than 14 years, is also the co-chairman of the Game Critics Awards, a group of 35 national journalists who present their "Best of E3" awards each June.  Based in Pacific Palisades, CA, he is a magna cum laude graduate from the University of Southern California. Most of his work is accessible through his website, GameSlice.com.</span></td>
